title: Create an Agent in Jenkins
tags: @zettel _method jenkins
roam-id: 6ac91e82-7323-4a22-a698-4b8486785552
type: text/markdown

- you need one jenkins master up and running
- you need to [[Generate an SSH Keypair]] on jenkins master
- on the other machine you want to make the agent, make sure you installed `java` on it.
- if it's ubuntu or debian [[Install Java on Ubuntu or Debian]]
- copy jenkins master's ssh public key to remote agent machine. see: [[Copy Public SSH Key to Another Machine]]
- add ssh credentials in jenkins
  - Kind: SSH Username with private key
  - Username: The SSH user on the agent
  - Private Key: Paste the private key from **jenkins master** `~/.ssh/id_rsa`
  - Optionally, set ID and description
- add a new node from jenkins ui and use the credentials above
- after succesfull agent creation don't forget to set built-in node's executors to 0
